Yobe State governor, Mai Mala Buni, has appointed Alhaji Abubakar Liman Baba as the general manager, Rural Water Supply and Sanitation Agency (RUWASA) with immediate effect. A statement issued and signed by the head of Service, Alhaji Muhammad B. Nura, said the appointment of Alhaji Abubakar Liman Baba was based on his years of experience, commitments and dedication to duty. “I have the pleasure to convey the approval of His Excellency, the executive governor of Yobe State, Hon Mai Mala Buni, for your appointment as general manager, Rural Water Supply and Sanitation Agency (RUWASA) with effect from 7th July, 2021. “Your appointment is based on your experience, commitment, dedication to duty and excellent record of performance. “While extending His Excellency’s best wishes over this well deserved appointment, it is our fervent hope that you will work even harder to justify the confidence reposed in you,” the statement said. Similarly, Governor Mai Mala Buni has approved the appointment of Alhaji Musa Audu Fara Fara as the Yobe State Accountant General. According to a statement issued by the head of Service, Alhaji Muhammad B. Nura said the appointment of Alhaji Musa Audu Fara Fara as the Yobe State Accountant General was also with immediate effect. 